By OKOSUN DENNIS
President Muhammadu Buhari on Sunday visited the Acting General Officer Commanding (GOC), 3 Division Nigerian Army, Brigadier General Mohammed Sani Aliyu, who is on admission at a hospital in Berlin, Germany.
Brig Gen Aliyu was involved in a road traffic accident on Tuesday, 8th March 2016, along Maiduguri-Damaturu road.
Brigadier General Aliyu survived the mishap and was stabilized before he was evacuated to Germany for further treatment.
It would be recalled that the head of Training and Operations of the Nigerian Army, Maj.-Gen. Yushaâ€™u Abubakar, died in the auto crash. Abubakar, was a former theatre commander of the Operation Lafiya Dole.
